    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix use-after-free vulnerability in signal_energy_fp2 function\n\n### Summary\nThere is a use-after-free vulnerability where freed memory is subsequently accessed downstream of function signal_energy_fp2 in openair1/PHY/TOOLS/signal_energy.c. The issue occurs when the function is called with a pointer to channel data that has been freed by free_channel_desc_scm but the calling code still attempts to use the result.\n\nThis fix adds defensive checks to prevent crashes when the function receives invalid pointers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/signal_energy.c`: Added NULL pointer and zero length validation to signal_energy_fp2 function\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/signal_energy.c`: Updated outdated comments referencing incorrect structure fields\n\n### Reproduction\nThe vulnerability can be triggered when:\n1. A channel descriptor is allocated and used normally\n2. free_channel_desc_scm is called to free the channel memory\n3. Downstream code still calls signal_energy_fp2 with the freed channel data pointer\n4. The function attempts to access the freed memory, causing a segmentation fault\n\nWith this fix, the function will safely return 0.0 instead of crashing when called with invalid parameters.\n"
}